<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-25T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-25T01:00:00-05:00" n="1109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1109">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4007.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-25T01:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1912—1 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>If you believe the letter to be really from Zapata, and representing his
                            real intentions, immediately inform President Madero, in strict
                            confidence. Also tell the Defense Committee of the Society of the
                            American Colony quickly and quietly to circulate the news among all
                            Americans so that if the attack is made they may gather at the selected
                            concentration points, where the American flag should be flown. No reply
                            should be made to Zapata. No part should be taken by Americans in
                            disorders unless urgently necessary for self-protection. Use your
                            discretion in informing other foreign colonies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>